		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> LOTR Q&A Rulings from 02/19/04<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.56)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=617'>Enrique "Max of Tat" Huerta</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=617&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> March 4, 2004</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Not for review.<br />
Originally posted 02/19/04 at<br />
http://www.decktech.net/lotr/featured/huerta.php<br />
================================================<br />
<br />
<br />
Hello All!!<br />
<br />
   Well, the Las Vegas Premier Series Event finally has a venue! In case you haven’t heard, all the fun will once again return to the Orleans Hotel and Casino. Siege of Gondor will not be legal for the Premier Series Event, so everyone knows what cards we can all expect to see. (Theoretically speaking anyway...) (= I have one more LOTR Q&A Rulings Update before the PSE, so be sure to get in your last minute rules questions!<br />
<br />
   I got a lot of questions this time around that I couldn’t answer. (No, not rulings questions!) For those that asked, I do not know what happened to your DeckTech article, why someone else can’t download software, and why I get more LOTR questions than SW. (= It reminds me of a Bart Simpson quote: &quot;Frankly, what you don’t know could just about fill a warehouse.&quot; And in my case, it would be a warehouse the size of the one from the end of Raider’s of the Lost Ark.<br />
<br />
   On to the questions!!! (=<br />
<br />
- Enrique<br />
<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Card Rulings:</h3><br />
<b>Hi! Just a Legolas Greenleaf question: He has the word &quot;Archer&quot; and the &quot;archery&quot; special ability. How do you use this card? How many wounds can this card inflict on one turn? Do you count him as an archer, figure out the total, then can you also use the special ability? For example...if you have Greenleaf in your fellowship and he’s the only card with the keyword archer, would you say &quot;the fellowship archery total is 1. Now, I’d like to exert him to wound a minion.&quot; Can you use the card like that? Thanks, [Eddie]</b><br />
<br />
Legolas is an archer which means he constantly adds 1 to the Free Peoples archery total. This is fine and dandy, but according to the rules, the Shadow player is the one that gets to decide where that archery wound goes, which makes it a little ineffective.<br />
<br />
However, Greenleaf has a special abilities that allowes him to instead of giving a normal archery wound, he can exert to wound any minion he wants (assuming the minion can take archery wounds). When he uses his special ability, he does not add 1 to the Free Peoples archery total like a normal archer. The other nice benefit of his special ability is that if he has enough vitality, he can exert more than once and deliver more wounds then a normal archer would.<br />
<br />
Basically, Greenleaf always adds to the archery total like a normal archer unless he uses his archery special ability.<br />
<br />
<b>Hello, Becoming a great fan of you. We have come to accept what you judge on any conflict. Thanks for all your time and concern. Here are a few questions:<br />
<br />
1- Smeagol is in a skirmish which ends up after the FPP &quot;adds a burden to make it take no wounds and +2&quot;. Smeagol looses the skirmish. There is also any theoden in play with kings mail and he loses the skirmish as well. Another companion dies triggering 4 threat wounds: <br />
a-Can FPP assign threat wounds on Smeagol? If he/she can, does smeagol take wounds?<br />
b-Can the FPP assign these threat wounds on Theoden and claim he takes no more than 1 wound?<br />
c- Can FPP assign these threat wounds on Frodo and take them as burdens, if Frodo has;<br />
i- Isildur’s Bane?<br />
ii- The Ruling Ring?<br />
iii- Answer to All Riddles? (I know it is impossible for &quot;Such A Weight to Carry&quot;)<br />
<br />
2- If there are only Frodo (with any ring), Smeagol and Sam (with Hobbit Sword) are in play and &quot;Balrog, Terror of Flame and Shadow&quot; is played, is Balrog NOT assigned to skirmishes? (probably the answer is yes but to be on the safe side...)<br />
Thanks in advance for your time and the answers. [Kirshamor]</b> <br />
<br />
Always great to have a fan. (=<br />
<br />
1. This is tricky, because you say one thing, but I think you might mean another. In either case, I’ll try to answer both.<br />
<br />
a1. Specifically, yes, Smeagol can take the threat wounds because the skimrish ability that was used to allow Smeagol to &quot;take no wounds&quot; only lasts for as long as THAT skirmish phase in which it was played. Once Smeagol’s skirmish is finished, he is not longer protected by that game text.<br />
<br />
a2. However, perhaps you decide to use Smeagol’s game text during the same skirmish in which another companion is going to die and trigger threats. In this case, Smeagol cannot take any of the threat wounds because his game text (which is not &quot;on&quot;) states that he takes no wounds.<br />
<br />
b. Theoden may only be assigned and take 1 wound because King’s Mail is always &quot;on&quot;. After he takes the first wound during that skirmish, be can not be assigned any further threat wounds. If you were to prevent that first wound (Eowyn, Lady of Rohan or Intimidate) then you could assign another wound to Theoden, but once he takes 1 wound, no more can be assigned to his during this skirmish phase.<br />
<br />
c.i.     Yes.<br />
c.ii.    Yes.<br />
c.iii.1  Similar to using the Answer to All Riddle with the Twilight Witch-king, Frodo needs to put on the Ring as a skimish action to protect him from wounds that occur later on during the same skirmish phase.<br />
<br />
c.iii.2  If Frodo had put the One Ring, Such A Weight To Carry on during the maneuver phase, it would still protect him on through the many skirmish phases. But he would have to have already put it on.<br />
<br />
2. Correct. If there isn’t a companion of strength 6 or greater, neither player may assign the Balrog, Terror of Flame and Shadow to a skirmish.<br />
<br />
<b>Only a single question. I was trying to find a counter card for the overpopular easterling decks and I saw &quot;Three Mountrous Trolls&quot; The game text says that everytime a shadow card is about to add any number of twilight tokens, you can exert a hobbit ally to prevent that. Can I prevent the ambush this way? Thanks a lot [Manuel] </b><br />
<br />
Yes. However, if a minion has multiple instances of Ambush, you would have to exert a Hobbit ally for each occurance of Ambush X. For example: If a Southron Fighter with Ambush 1 was bearing a Raider Bow (making him Ambush 5), and the FPP assigned him to a skirmish, you would need to exert a Hobbit ally once, for the Ambush 1 and once for the Ambush 5.<br />
<br />
<b>This is a pretty basic question, here goes: You can return Merry to hand by spotting 0 possessions, but can you return Pippin to your hand by wounding an imaginary roaming minion twice? [Urthanz]</b><br />
<br />
Yes, the only requirements for Merry and Pippin is that they are not assigned to a skirmish. As long as you pay the costs (returning them to hand) you can carry out as much of the effect as possible and ignore the rest. If there are no roaming minions, that doesn’t prevent you for returning Pippin to hand.<br />
<br />
(NOTE: Normally you can not &quot;ignore the rest&quot; when playing a card from your hand or discard pile. But Merry’s game text states &quot;up to 2 [Rohan] possessions&quot; so you can choose to play 0. If it did not say &quot;up to&quot; you would not be able to return Merry if there were 0 possesions in the discard pile.)<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Game/Tournament Rulings:</h3><br />
<b>Hey Enrique, Have they made a ruling on Smeagol that pumps by adding burdens versus a minion at Anduin Banks? This is happened disturbingly often to me and I want to know how the infinite loop is supposed to end. It’s really important to get a ruling on this I think since it’s getting to be a pain hearing one million different unofficial solutions. thanks buddy :)  [Patrick Sullivan]<br />
<br />
Hey Enrique. The new SOG site 7, Osgiliath Channel, can you FORCE the free peoples player to move again if he/she has already double-moved? Usually they make some mention of ’...if the move limit allows...’ but this one doesn’t. thanks, enrique... [Patrick Sullivan] </b><br />
<br />
1. As mentioned before, usually the situation with Slinker and Anduin Backs (4K) can be handled by looking at the skirmish without either player using Slinker’s or Anduin Bank’s (4K) game text. If the minion is winning the skirmish without anything else, then the minion will still win the skirmish. If Smeagol is winning the skirmish without anything else, then Smegol will still win the skirmish.<br />
<br />
The only difference is in the case of overwhelming. If it looks like one of the characters is going to be overwhelmed, I would allow a few iterations of the loops to prove overwhelming will not occur, then determine the winner of the skirmish from there.<br />
<br />
2. Although it’s not specifically stated, if the Fellowship has reached their move limit, Osgiliath Channel will not make the FPP move again. This based on the rule of completing as much of an effect as possible and ignoring the rest.<br />
<br />
<b>Hi Enrique, another couple of questions, slightly annoying perhaps but it’s hard to find clear answers! :D<br />
<br />
In the archery phase, in archery actions, the shadow adds to the archery total (say, cloud of arrows).  The free peoples kills all the shadow players minions in archery actions. <br />
Do we then add up the archery totals, finish the archery phase before we skip to regroup phase? Or do we have to immediately skip to the regroup phase when minions are all gone?<br />
<br />
Also, on a minor note, i can’t find in any rules documents (even on deciphers ’comphrehensive’ rulebook online) about the mulligans rule; draw 8 cards at the start, if you don’t like em, drop em and draw 6. I just wanted to make sure they are shuffled in, and not put on the bottom of the draw deck.  Sorry, just can’t find it anywhere! :)<br />
<br />
I know i shouldn’t ask, but Trust Me is frustrating me.  <br />
Just to clear it up (and i’ve read your rulings, just the current rulings document makes it a bit confusing), if there are 3 minions assigned to 3 different companions, this means there will be 3 skirmish phases, plus two fierces skirmish phases if two were fierce, right? That means i could exert 5 times over the skirmishing, to give each skirmisher plus 3 strength if i could spot 3 signets?<br />
<br />
the crd says if you spot 2 signets, you could give one companion +2, and another one +1... why would they say that unless it means a total of plus +3 is the limit over the whole skirmishing business, thus treating ONE skirmish PHASE as several skirmishes?<br />
<br />
I’m sorry for asking these questions, because they’ve been asked a million times, well at least trust me has anyways. cheers! [Machine]<br />
<br />
Sorry Enrique, one more question:<br />
<br />
The southron guys who wound in the assignment phase (when assigned and have initiative, wound their opponent), that’s obviously in the assignement phase - so the ruling ring cannot be used as a response?? [Machine]</b><br />
<br />
1. You always complete the archery phase before you jump to the regroup phase. So if the Shadow was able to add to the archery total (Cloud of Arrows or Weapons of Isengard) the FPP would still have to take those archery wounds. NOTE the difference between those cards and Orc Bowmen. Orc Bowmen only add while there is a [Sauron] Minion to spot. If there are no minions, there is not bonus.<br />
<br />
2. The mulligan rule is a tournament rule and can be found in the LOTR tournament guidelines (pg 6).<br />
<br />
3. Assuming you have enough exertions, yes.<br />
<br />
4. Here’s a better explination of that example. The limit and example is there to clarify whether you can add +2 to one companion, and then +2 to another companion during the same skirmish as a way to get around the limit +3. It only really would be worthwhile when used with Merry, Friend of Sam. (Because Merry could exert twice to add his strength to the skimirshing companion.) The +2 to the companion and the +2 to Merry would give the original companion a +4 and get around the limit.<br />
<br />
5. So, just to clarify, the limit of +3 is regardless of either it all goes to the same companion or different companions during the same Skirmish phase. If it’s done during different skirmish phases, that is fine.<br />
<br />
6. Correct. The wound occurs during the assignment phase and the Ruling Rule would not be able to be put on as a response to those wounds.<br />
<br />
<b>Ok, since I never get a response from Elrond to any questions anymore, I have a question on timing and threat wounds. Is the assignment of threat wounds a part of the skirmish that killed the companion or is it a response to the companion hitting the grave? [Jeffrey]</b><br />
<br />
The answer is YES to both questions.<br />
<br />
If a companion dies as a result of wounds received for losing a skirmishimmer is still part of the skirmish phase. Threats are triggered when the companion goes to the Dead Pile. This means that cards like the Ruling Ring, Armor, Gimli’s Helm, and Faramir, A Wizard’s Pupil are still in effect. Only after all responses to winning or losing a skirmish and all &quot;end of skirmish actions&quot; have resolved, does an individual skirmish phase end.<br />
<br />
<h3>Star Wars:CCG Rulings</h3><br />
<br />
None this update.<br />
<br />
- Enrique<br />
